WEBVTT

1
00:00:45.119 --> 00:00:48.029
- My goodness. - Why do they have to be so cute?

2
00:00:48.029 --> 00:00:49.059
My gosh.

3
00:00:50.959 --> 00:00:52.200
I won't get bewitched by you guys.

4
00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:54.459
Why are you talking to yourself?

5
00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:02.040
I thought you did aerobics, but it looks like you're in a circus.

6
00:01:02.110 --> 00:01:05.580
I need to dress in fancy colors to stand out. You know nothing.

7
00:01:05.810 --> 00:01:06.809
What are you doing here?

8
00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:08.080
Mom.

9
00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:10.150
Let's go on a date.

10
00:01:10.150 --> 00:01:11.879
What will you buy for me?

11
00:01:12.150 --> 00:01:13.919
Just hurry up and get changed.

12
00:01:15.419 --> 00:01:16.589
Make sure you get changed, okay?

13
00:01:32.470 --> 00:01:33.570
Is this it?

14
00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:36.239
- Buy me more. - No, stop

15
00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:37.640
We bought enough.

16
00:01:49.720 --> 00:01:51.190
My goodness, come here.

17
00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:21.220
Ever since I was young, I thought there'd be a secret to my birth.

18
00:02:21.220 --> 00:02:23.349
I guess I was right. A real mother wouldn't have done this.

19
00:02:23.819 --> 00:02:25.489
If I wasn't your real mom,

20
00:02:25.489 --> 00:02:27.289
I wouldn't have bought you something so expensive.

21
00:02:27.360 --> 00:02:29.560
It looks so fancy and beautiful on you.

22
00:02:29.690 --> 00:02:31.060
It suits you so well.

23
00:02:31.230 --> 00:02:33.530
Whatever. You're just sorry.

24
00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:35.470
Let's say I bought you that because I felt sorry.

25
00:02:36.129 --> 00:02:38.970
But what about you? Why did you buy me all these gifts?

26
00:02:39.370 --> 00:02:41.340
Did you get yourself in trouble?

27
00:02:42.609 --> 00:02:44.940
Gosh, no. Why would I get myself in trouble?

28
00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:47.240
Why don't you ever get yourself in trouble?

29
00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:49.810
You're almost 40. You should be more adventurous.

30
00:02:49.810 --> 00:02:52.050
You're too honest and kind.

31
00:02:52.550 --> 00:02:53.819
My goodness.

32
00:02:55.690 --> 00:02:58.490
Then I guess I should get myself in big trouble.

33
00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:00.889
You'd better not change your mind.

34
00:03:02.060 --> 00:03:03.490
Promise me.

35
00:03:03.490 --> 00:03:05.300
Why do I need to promise? What's with you?

36
00:03:06.759 --> 00:03:08.569
I made up my mind.

37
00:03:08.599 --> 00:03:10.199
And I hope you cooperate.

38
00:03:21.949 --> 00:03:23.250
Hey. You guys.

39
00:03:23.680 --> 00:03:27.220
Can you not fight today? I even baked cookies for you guys.

40
00:03:27.250 --> 00:03:29.250
- You know how to bake cookies? - Sit down.

41
00:03:33.990 --> 00:03:35.659
Did you bake it with dirt?

42
00:03:35.659 --> 00:03:38.930
You're such a picky eater unlike how you look.

43
00:03:42.069 --> 00:03:44.030
Let's order pig trotters.

44
00:03:44.030 --> 00:03:45.639
Pig trotters, my foot.

45
00:03:45.639 --> 00:03:48.039
It's a special party. Let's order chicken.

46
00:03:48.039 --> 00:03:49.840
I haven't been out in three months.

47
00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:51.840
I haven't had fun for six months.

48
00:03:53.379 --> 00:03:56.310
I've been craving pig trotters for a few months now.

49
00:03:56.479 --> 00:04:00.379
Every day, I tell myself that I'll eat pig trotters tonight.

50
00:04:00.849 --> 00:04:02.050
I promise myself that.

51
00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:05.020
But once I clean the house, clean after the kids,

52
00:04:05.020 --> 00:04:08.789
cook dinner for my husband, and eat the leftover food,

53
00:04:08.789 --> 00:04:10.690
I suddenly lose my appetite.

54
00:04:10.690 --> 00:04:13.030
That's why I still haven't had pig trotters.

55
00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:14.729
And in three hours,

56
00:04:14.729 --> 00:04:16.400
I'll be back in a world where there are no pig trotters.

57
00:04:17.699 --> 00:04:19.199
- Order pig trotters. - Got it.

58
00:04:19.199 --> 00:04:21.069
Yes, order chicken.

59
00:04:23.139 --> 00:04:26.039
Why do you have to be friends with a guy like him?

60
00:04:26.039 --> 00:04:28.680
We were friends first. You came later.

61
00:04:29.050 --> 00:04:31.849
Darn you. You're so annoying.

62
00:04:34.919 --> 00:04:37.020
What's with her? Is she bipolar?

63
00:04:37.020 --> 00:04:39.620
Don't mess with her. She has twin boys.

64
00:04:39.620 --> 00:04:41.060
My goodness.

65
00:04:43.859 --> 00:04:47.060
Look at you. Are you an alcoholic?

66
00:04:47.199 --> 00:04:49.270
I think so. He got divorced, you know

67
00:04:50.629 --> 00:04:51.670
I can hear you.

68
00:04:52.100 --> 00:04:54.370
- Just order pig trotters. - Order chicken.

69
00:04:54.370 --> 00:04:55.709
- Pig trotters! - Chicken!

70
00:04:55.709 --> 00:04:57.069
- Trotters. - Fried chicken.

71
00:04:57.069 --> 00:04:58.579
- Trotters. - Fried chicken.

72
00:04:58.579 --> 00:04:59.610
I...

73
00:04:59.610 --> 00:05:01.480
Shut it, both of you.

74
00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:04.379
Before I order one of the two,

75
00:05:04.779 --> 00:05:06.550
I have an announcement to make.

76
00:05:06.550 --> 00:05:08.790
First, fill your glasses.

77
00:05:17.060 --> 00:05:18.560
This party...

78
00:05:19.329 --> 00:05:22.500
is to celebrate the second chapter of my life.

79
00:05:23.129 --> 00:05:26.000
I, Jang Ha Ri, have decided not to get married.

80
00:05:30.240 --> 00:05:32.910
Guys, why aren't you saying anything?

81
00:05:35.649 --> 00:05:39.079
Whether you announce it or not,

82
00:05:39.180 --> 00:05:41.850
it's not really up to you.

83
00:05:42.219 --> 00:05:45.620
Take me for instance. I grew up never wanting to get married.

84
00:05:45.759 --> 00:05:50.160
All I agreed to was a cup of coffee, but look at where I am now.

85
00:05:50.860 --> 00:05:52.230
What's there to announce?

86
00:05:52.329 --> 00:05:54.759
There was a slim chance of you getting married anyway.

87
00:05:55.529 --> 00:05:57.399
Is this because of that blind date?

88
00:05:57.699 --> 00:06:02.440
No, that didn't go any further because we weren't compatible.

89
00:06:02.610 --> 00:06:04.670
- Unbelievable. - Do you have dementia?

90
00:06:04.839 --> 00:06:05.910
Have you forgotten...

91
00:06:06.110 --> 00:06:08.209
that you were never the dating type?

92
00:06:09.579 --> 00:06:10.649
Don't you remember?

93
00:06:14.949 --> 00:06:16.019
Ms. Jang?

94
00:06:17.550 --> 00:06:20.889
- Gosh, what brings you here? - I had business nearby.

95
00:06:20.889 --> 00:06:23.389
Anyway, I've been meaning to call you.

96
00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:27.730
But that would've been a mistake since you have a boyfriend.

97
00:06:28.170 --> 00:06:30.569
He's just a friend. The son of my mom's friend.

98
00:06:31.170 --> 00:06:32.300
Is that so?

99
00:06:32.500 --> 00:06:35.639
Right, then are you free this weekend?

100
00:06:36.139 --> 00:06:38.579
I have tickets to a musical if you're up for it.

101
00:06:38.779 --> 00:06:40.040
I'll even buy dinner.

102
00:06:40.910 --> 00:06:44.180
A deadline is coming up for me, so maybe you can take someone else.

103
00:06:45.879 --> 00:06:50.319
The tickets are until this month. Would you be available?

104
00:06:51.490 --> 00:06:53.490
I don't want to make a promise I can't keep.

105
00:06:53.990 --> 00:06:56.430
By the way, did you see the announcement I sent out?

106
00:06:57.759 --> 00:07:00.259
I'll have Mr. Kim look at it.

107
00:07:00.259 --> 00:07:02.629
He'll now be taking over.

108
00:07:02.699 --> 00:07:04.829
- I'll see you around. - You too.

109
00:07:07.569 --> 00:07:08.769
What the...

110
00:07:10.769 --> 00:07:13.910
He just asked you out on a date, you moron.

111
00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:15.579
When will you ever learn?

112
00:07:17.449 --> 00:07:21.079
This is why I never wanted to set you up with anyone.

113
00:07:23.290 --> 00:07:26.219
I was clueless back then.

114
00:07:26.319 --> 00:07:29.990
No, your DNA has been wired this way.

115
00:07:30.430 --> 00:07:31.829
You're right.

116
00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:33.160
I've never been good at dating...

117
00:07:33.430 --> 00:07:35.329
and marriage is a long-shot for me.

118
00:07:35.469 --> 00:07:36.600
So what?

119
00:07:36.600 --> 00:07:38.600
There are more things we can't do compared to the ones we can.

120
00:07:38.870 --> 00:07:41.440
Then why have you been desperate to get married?

121
00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:42.670
Gosh.

122
00:07:42.769 --> 00:07:45.009
You know what? Good for you.

123
00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:49.079
Marriage only leads to a dishtowel or a rag in your hand.

124
00:07:49.180 --> 00:07:50.579
Just like you have been so far,

125
00:07:50.579 --> 00:07:51.779
live your life with a laptop in one hand...

126
00:07:51.779 --> 00:07:54.350
and a take-out coffee in another.

127
00:07:55.690 --> 00:08:00.319
Right. Well, thanks for your sincere support.

128
00:08:04.490 --> 00:08:07.560
Anyway, there's something else I wanted to tell you.

129
00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:11.969
Hold on. But I've received so many monetary gifts from you.

130
00:08:12.269 --> 00:08:15.339
You know what? I'll buy you something for this occasion.

131
00:08:15.639 --> 00:08:17.240
Tell me whatever you need.

132
00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:19.839
That's not necessary. Save it for yourself.

133
00:08:19.839 --> 00:08:22.610
- It's not even important. - Just take it.

134
00:08:22.680 --> 00:08:25.879
This is probably your last chance to receive any celebratory gift.

135
00:08:26.019 --> 00:08:27.579
Zip it...

136
00:08:27.579 --> 00:08:29.589
or you'll taste my foot in your mouth.

137
00:08:31.290 --> 00:08:34.719
Anyway, I...

138
00:08:35.060 --> 00:08:37.829
So did you order the trotters?

139
00:08:37.829 --> 00:08:39.259
Fried chicken comes first.

140
00:08:39.259 --> 00:08:40.959
Order the trotters right away.

141
00:08:40.959 --> 00:08:43.769
- No, fried chicken. - Trotters.

142
00:08:43.769 --> 00:08:44.969
Fried chicken!

143
00:08:45.399 --> 00:08:48.000
- You two... - No to trotters!

144
00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:50.310
- You two! - Fine, I'll order it myself.

145
00:08:50.310 --> 00:08:53.180
- Trotters are what I love. - Unbelievable.

146
00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:55.509
- I have no one looking out for me. - You jerk.

147
00:08:57.449 --> 00:09:00.120
(Hangang Library)

148
00:09:19.670 --> 00:09:22.369
("Pregnancy for Endometriosis Patients")

149
00:09:26.040 --> 00:09:28.109
(The chances of a natural pregnancy)

150
00:09:28.109 --> 00:09:34.719
(Hormones, Drug treatment, Surgery, Intracytoplasmic sperm injection)

151
00:09:34.719 --> 00:09:41.930
(The chances of a natural pregnancy is about 15 percent.)

152
00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:50.400
(4. Ethical issues)

153
00:09:54.199 --> 00:09:55.410
You can't receive infertility treatments...

154
00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:56.540
unless you're married.

155
00:09:57.010 --> 00:09:59.440
The only exceptions are for women in a de facto marriage.

156
00:09:59.609 --> 00:10:02.680
You need a spouse's consent to receive sperm from a donor.

157
00:10:03.410 --> 00:10:06.819
So what's the best way to get pregnant within six months?

158
00:10:09.249 --> 00:10:13.790
You can marry a man and get pregnant with him...

159
00:10:14.260 --> 00:10:15.829
or...

160
00:10:20.329 --> 00:10:23.469
find some random guy and get knocked up.

161
00:10:26.670 --> 00:10:30.270
What happens if I have the baby without his knowledge...

162
00:10:30.670 --> 00:10:34.239
and he finds out that I lied about it?

163
00:10:35.579 --> 00:10:36.650
Well...

164
00:10:39.280 --> 00:10:41.020
It's like the storyline of my favorite soap opera.

165
00:10:45.190 --> 00:10:49.859
Anyway, an unmarried woman can't find a sperm donor in Korea.

166
00:10:50.130 --> 00:10:53.229
There aren't many donors for even all the infertile couples.

167
00:10:53.229 --> 00:10:56.630
I'm also a patient who was diagnosed as infertile.

168
00:10:56.630 --> 00:10:58.699
The law is against it, so you must find another way.

169
00:10:58.969 --> 00:11:01.300
- I must find another way? - That's right.

170
00:11:02.069 --> 00:11:03.209
On your own.

171
00:11:21.589 --> 00:11:23.790
(Han Se Sang)

172
00:11:29.569 --> 00:11:32.670
- It's me. - Why haven't you been picking up?

173
00:11:33.670 --> 00:11:36.069
- How was the move? - Fine.

174
00:11:37.040 --> 00:11:38.910
It's the anniversary of dad's death next Wednesday.

175
00:11:40.609 --> 00:11:41.739
I know.

176
00:11:42.609 --> 00:11:43.680
You'll be there, right?

177
00:11:45.479 --> 00:11:46.579
Sure.

178
00:11:48.050 --> 00:11:49.520
Be there. Mom's hoping to see you.

179
00:12:07.140 --> 00:12:08.199
Ms. Jang.

180
00:12:13.140 --> 00:12:14.680
Are you still embarrassed to see me?

181
00:12:21.479 --> 00:12:23.619
No, I couldn't be more comfortable around you.

182
00:12:23.619 --> 00:12:25.690
Is that so? Me too.

183
00:12:34.329 --> 00:12:36.199
What? What now?

184
00:12:40.339 --> 00:12:42.670
Thank you for working with us on the cover.

185
00:12:46.239 --> 00:12:48.310
Let me thank you for the car ride with a meal.

186
00:12:49.810 --> 00:12:51.920
Just tell me what it is you want.

187
00:12:51.920 --> 00:12:54.249
It's not like we're close enough to communicate through gazes.

188
00:12:57.790 --> 00:13:00.589
I got it. I take back what I said about avoiding you.

189
00:13:00.790 --> 00:13:02.989
- Bingo. - Gosh, I'm smart.

190
00:13:03.790 --> 00:13:05.329
Like I said...

191
00:13:12.199 --> 00:13:13.369
Was I tricked just now?

192
00:13:16.940 --> 00:13:18.040
Unbelievable.

193
00:13:25.079 --> 00:13:26.219
Sorry, everyone.

194
00:13:28.219 --> 00:13:30.150
- Be more punctual. - Sure thing.

195
00:13:33.760 --> 00:13:35.790
"How Won Bin and Lee Na Young raise their son."

196
00:13:35.790 --> 00:13:36.790
(Special Interview with Won Bin and Lee Na Young)

197
00:13:37.859 --> 00:13:39.530
How exactly do they raise their son?

198
00:13:40.060 --> 00:13:42.530
- I'll meet them and ask. - How do you expect to do that?

199
00:13:43.069 --> 00:13:44.430
I'll try and schedule an interview.

200
00:13:45.400 --> 00:13:46.400
Go ahead. Who knows?

201
00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:48.940
We might have our first sold-out issue thanks to you.

202
00:13:49.270 --> 00:13:50.339
Yes, boss.

203
00:13:50.339 --> 00:13:52.140
Interviewing celebrities...

204
00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:54.640
won't help you get hired at a fashion magazine.

205
00:13:54.640 --> 00:13:58.050
Suggest items that are doable, not those that are a dream of yours.

206
00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:00.979
Next.

207
00:14:01.819 --> 00:14:03.619
Where are we on the search for a columnist?

208
00:14:04.249 --> 00:14:06.859
What about that friend who's living off you and your mom?

209
00:14:06.859 --> 00:14:08.859
He's a single dad with a decent enough profile.

210
00:14:09.160 --> 00:14:10.859
- Yoon Jae Young? - Yes.

211
00:14:15.369 --> 00:14:16.670
But he's clueless.

212
00:14:17.469 --> 00:14:19.300
Well, Sung Woo will be here.

213
00:14:19.569 --> 00:14:20.670
Sung Woo too?

214
00:14:21.569 --> 00:14:25.069
Do Ah, would you like some baby food?

215
00:14:26.010 --> 00:14:29.479
Or how about this since you're older now?

216
00:14:29.780 --> 00:14:31.410
I'm sure you're old enough for this.

217
00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:34.219
He's a fun character.

218
00:14:34.520 --> 00:14:37.719
It's better to feature a mess than an expert in childrearing.

219
00:14:37.719 --> 00:14:38.790
Try to get him on board.

220
00:14:39.359 --> 00:14:41.859
Since I'm back, we should grab some dinner.

221
00:14:42.060 --> 00:14:43.459
Ask when the Advertising Department...

222
00:14:43.459 --> 00:14:44.859
and the people at the studio will be free.

223
00:14:45.229 --> 00:14:46.729
Can we go to my favorite restaurant?

224
00:14:46.729 --> 00:14:47.800
I'll book it myself.

225
00:14:48.900 --> 00:14:50.770
How about we get some raw fish?

226
00:14:51.630 --> 00:14:53.599
- No, Korean beef barbecue. - What?

227
00:14:53.599 --> 00:14:55.140
They're clueless, aren't they?

228
00:14:55.140 --> 00:14:57.709
- Sushi. - We should eat beef.

229
00:14:57.709 --> 00:14:59.910
- But it's a company dinner. - Come now. We should get sushi.

230
00:14:59.910 --> 00:15:02.180
(Infertility Forum: Success Stories)

231
00:15:03.079 --> 00:15:04.680
Here's your food.

232
00:15:04.849 --> 00:15:06.550
Do Ah, do you want to eat this?

233
00:15:07.819 --> 00:15:08.819
Or this?

234
00:15:08.849 --> 00:15:10.589
Trust Daddy, okay?

235
00:15:10.890 --> 00:15:13.020
Brand name foods are the best.

236
00:15:18.729 --> 00:15:20.260
I smell cheonggukjang.

237
00:15:24.599 --> 00:15:26.640
You pooped, didn't you?

238
00:15:30.270 --> 00:15:31.440
Wipes.

239
00:15:39.749 --> 00:15:41.380
Let's go in. Hold on.

240
00:15:41.520 --> 00:15:44.989
Why isn't there a changing table in the men's room?

241
00:15:52.499 --> 00:15:55.099
There it is. Hold on. Good girl.

242
00:15:55.430 --> 00:15:56.670
Good.

243
00:15:56.729 --> 00:15:57.869
We're here.

244
00:16:01.270 --> 00:16:02.410
It's full.

245
00:16:05.739 --> 00:16:08.479
- What's wrong with you? - I'm sorry.

246
00:16:16.520 --> 00:16:18.219
It's okay.

247
00:16:30.130 --> 00:16:32.270
We're home. It's okay.

248
00:16:32.300 --> 00:16:33.900
Daddy's sorry. Hold on.

249
00:16:37.140 --> 00:16:39.010
Sorry. Daddy's sorry.

250
00:16:46.119 --> 00:16:47.280
You must be embarrassed.

251
00:16:47.280 --> 00:16:49.650
Daddy's sorry. I'll change your diaper quickly.

252
00:16:53.760 --> 00:16:56.729
Mister. Are you raising a baby on the street?

253
00:16:56.930 --> 00:16:59.030
- What? - What did the baby do wrong?

254
00:16:59.530 --> 00:17:02.300
Don't use the stroller for garbage.

255
00:17:02.300 --> 00:17:03.869
Put the baby in it.

256
00:17:04.670 --> 00:17:06.569
That's not mine. It's his.

257
00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:07.869
Is it your friend's?

258
00:17:07.900 --> 00:17:09.310
He isn't my friend.

259
00:17:09.310 --> 00:17:10.739
He must be from a different district.

260
00:17:15.579 --> 00:17:17.280
Look.

261
00:17:18.180 --> 00:17:20.180
