00:51:22.810 --> 00:51:25.980
Should I live alone without any family,

794
00:51:25.980 --> 00:51:28.290
living just for myself, and then die alone?

795
00:51:34.020 --> 00:51:35.989
I want to live for someone too.

796
00:51:42.829 --> 00:51:44.099
You crazy witch.

797
00:51:44.869 --> 00:51:47.610
You saw how I lived.

798
00:51:47.940 --> 00:51:51.440
How could you even think about having a kid alone?

799
00:51:51.440 --> 00:51:53.840
You should think about being happily married!

800
00:51:55.509 --> 00:51:57.719
You raised me just fine without a husband.

801
00:51:58.179 --> 00:52:00.679
No. It was hard even when Dad was around.

802
00:52:01.790 --> 00:52:04.420
I grew up watching you and Dad fight all the time.

803
00:52:05.020 --> 00:52:07.360
You only showed me that marriage makes you sad.

804
00:52:07.360 --> 00:52:08.889
Why are you telling me to do something you couldn't?

805
00:52:08.989 --> 00:52:10.460
Is it my fault you're not married?

806
00:52:10.759 --> 00:52:13.000
Did I tell you to learn from me?

807
00:52:13.259 --> 00:52:14.969
Why is it my fault that your life is messed up?

808
00:52:14.969 --> 00:52:16.500
Why is my life messed up?

809
00:52:18.270 --> 00:52:19.969
Is it messed up not to get married in case...

810
00:52:19.969 --> 00:52:21.670
- I end up like you? - Hey.

811
00:52:22.509 --> 00:52:23.670
That's enough.

812
00:52:25.040 --> 00:52:27.710
Auntie. Calm down. Let's talk about it tomorrow.

813
00:52:29.049 --> 00:52:30.150
Get out.

814
00:52:30.150 --> 00:52:33.219
Don't learn from me and ruin your life.

815
00:52:33.579 --> 00:52:36.849
You're smart, so get out and live as you want.

816
00:52:36.849 --> 00:52:39.759
Get out. Get out.

817
00:52:40.119 --> 00:52:41.690
Get out right now! Get out.

818
00:52:42.560 --> 00:52:43.730
Wait outside.

819
00:53:50.230 --> 00:53:52.699
- Are you okay? - Yes.

820
00:54:26.500 --> 00:54:27.560
Don't cry.

821
00:54:32.799 --> 00:54:34.299
What are you doing?

822
00:54:37.040 --> 00:54:40.279
You said this is what I should do when someone cries.

823
00:54:45.849 --> 00:54:46.849
I'm not a kid.

824
00:54:49.820 --> 00:54:51.020
You look like one right now.

825
00:55:12.909 --> 00:55:14.110
Thanks.

826
00:55:20.820 --> 00:55:23.619
Please don't ask me what happened.

827
00:55:24.090 --> 00:55:25.389
I wasn't going to.

828
00:55:25.790 --> 00:55:28.130
I figured it might be too embarrassing for you.

829
00:55:29.829 --> 00:55:32.000
I'm so pathetic.

830
00:55:32.500 --> 00:55:36.469
I'm about to turn 40, but I'm still so immature.

831
00:55:37.270 --> 00:55:38.570
You're good as long as...

832
00:55:38.869 --> 00:55:41.540
you didn't run outside after you got scolded by your mom.

833
00:55:44.340 --> 00:55:45.940
I'm 41.

834
00:55:47.380 --> 00:55:49.179
But I still don't know what it means to be an adult.

835
00:55:50.009 --> 00:55:53.079
My body keeps aging, but my heart is still young.

836
00:55:54.219 --> 00:55:56.119
When I see something nice, I want to have it.

837
00:55:56.320 --> 00:55:58.360
When someone offends me, I get angry.

838
00:55:58.790 --> 00:56:00.659
When I suffer a loss, I feel upset.

839
00:56:01.730 --> 00:56:03.759
I still feel everything I felt as a kid.

840
00:56:04.130 --> 00:56:05.900
So I don't get what's so different about being 40.

841
00:56:09.670 --> 00:56:11.840
There's nothing good about aging.

842
00:56:12.440 --> 00:56:15.509
But if I have to choose, I guess the only good thing...

843
00:56:17.009 --> 00:56:18.710
is that I have a better judgment of character.

844
00:56:22.179 --> 00:56:24.980
Even if you were that weird lady on TV,

845
00:56:26.750 --> 00:56:27.779
I know for a fact...

846
00:56:31.420 --> 00:56:35.290
that you're a good person.

847
00:56:38.299 --> 00:56:39.500
Ha Ri.

848
00:56:53.310 --> 00:56:55.579
What are you doing out here after fighting with your mom?

849
00:56:56.150 --> 00:56:57.849
I didn't fight with my mom.

850
00:57:01.750 --> 00:57:02.790
We meet again.

851
00:57:04.119 --> 00:57:06.489
You didn't have to come looking for me. I was going to go home.

852
00:57:06.489 --> 00:57:08.759
Why did you wear my slippers?

853
00:57:08.759 --> 00:57:10.630
They're expensive. They're my favorite.

854
00:57:10.630 --> 00:57:11.730
Hurry up and wear your shoes.

855
00:57:17.029 --> 00:57:18.299
What are you doing?

856
00:57:22.170 --> 00:57:24.170
What? Hurry up so we can go home.

857
00:57:26.840 --> 00:57:27.949
Let's go.

858
00:57:29.409 --> 00:57:30.849
We live together.

859
00:57:32.049 --> 00:57:33.820
- What are you saying? - Let's go.

860
00:57:35.020 --> 00:57:36.520
Why are you so loud?

861
00:57:36.520 --> 00:57:37.989
- I'm not loud. - Be quiet!

862
00:57:37.989 --> 00:57:39.320
I'm the quietest person on earth.

863
00:57:57.170 --> 00:58:00.179
I can't believe you were talking to a guy after you ran out like that.

864
00:58:00.279 --> 00:58:02.449
Do you really have to say it like that?

865
00:58:02.449 --> 00:58:05.179
I've had enough for today. Let's just walk home quietly.

866
00:58:15.329 --> 00:58:16.960
I'm not being sarcastic.

867
00:58:18.400 --> 00:58:20.000
Don't care about what others say.

868
00:58:20.860 --> 00:58:24.099
I'm just saying you should do whatever you want...

869
00:58:24.400 --> 00:58:25.969
regardless of what others might think.

870
00:58:27.070 --> 00:58:29.210
What's with you? I'll see you.

871
00:58:29.770 --> 00:58:31.170
I quit working at the hospital.

872
00:58:34.480 --> 00:58:36.250
But you still have some time until your leave is over.

873
00:58:36.679 --> 00:58:37.849
I thought you wanted to become a professor.

874
00:58:38.320 --> 00:58:41.520
I won't have time to do lectures, treat patients,

875
00:58:41.520 --> 00:58:43.520
and write theses.

876
00:58:43.989 --> 00:58:47.259
I feel so upset that I can't get to do what I wanted.

877
00:58:48.690 --> 00:58:50.659
But what can I do? I'll just have to get by.

878
00:58:52.099 --> 00:58:53.699
How exactly?

879
00:58:53.960 --> 00:58:55.099
I'm going to open up a hospital...

880
00:58:55.099 --> 00:58:56.270
with the money I got from selling my apartment.

881
00:58:56.799 --> 00:58:58.540
That's why I moved into your place.

882
00:58:59.440 --> 00:59:03.310
I've been wasting away my life after I was left with Do Ah.

883
00:59:03.969 --> 00:59:05.880
But funnily enough, I found myself...

884
00:59:06.380 --> 00:59:07.779
gaining strength from her.

885
00:59:10.679 --> 00:59:12.719
I know it's hard for me to fully understand you.

886
00:59:13.619 --> 00:59:15.820
But if you need someone,

887
00:59:16.290 --> 00:59:18.389
and you want that to be a baby, I'd understand.

888
00:59:24.290 --> 00:59:25.460
I'm also a dad.

889
00:59:26.199 --> 00:59:29.130
And you're probably doing your best to get by just like me.

890
00:59:32.770 --> 00:59:34.000
I'll publish an interview about your hospital...

891
00:59:34.000 --> 00:59:35.310
to congratulate your grand opening.

892
00:59:35.670 --> 00:59:38.079
It'll be a series. You can give medical consultations.

893
00:59:38.079 --> 00:59:39.210
Sure.

894
00:59:40.279 --> 00:59:41.980
But wait a minute.

895
00:59:42.349 --> 00:59:43.650
I will...

896
00:59:45.880 --> 00:59:47.549
do it if you let Do Ah participate.

897
00:59:48.219 --> 00:59:49.219
Mr. Yoon.

898
00:59:50.520 --> 00:59:52.389
Not everyone thinks Do Ah is adorable.

899
00:59:52.389 --> 00:59:55.159
What are you talking about? She takes after me.

900
00:59:55.159 --> 00:59:57.889
- That's her flaw. Now, go home. - My goodness.

901
01:00:13.210 --> 01:00:15.610
I'm going to go do an interview.

902
01:00:15.610 --> 01:00:18.219
Where are you going? You have something to tell me.

903
01:00:19.020 --> 01:00:21.549
- No, I don't. - Yes, you do.

904
01:00:21.549 --> 01:00:22.650
Go inside the meeting room.

905
01:00:23.049 --> 01:00:24.349
Hey, wait.

906
01:00:24.619 --> 01:00:27.090
You didn't shoot the probiotics ad yet, did you?

907
01:00:27.159 --> 01:00:28.630
- Why? - They want a doctor...

908
01:00:28.630 --> 01:00:29.759
to recommend the product.

909
01:00:29.929 --> 01:00:31.230
You know a pediatrician, right?

910
01:00:31.230 --> 01:00:34.130
Yes, of course. I know a very nice pediatrician.

911
01:00:35.170 --> 01:00:36.299
I'll go bring him.

912
01:00:38.699 --> 01:00:40.369
Why don't you just call?

913
01:00:41.739 --> 01:00:43.110
Does she prefer to meet people face to face?

914
01:00:44.509 --> 01:00:45.610
Don't ask.

915
01:00:50.449 --> 01:00:51.520
Okay, great.

916
01:00:52.679 --> 01:00:53.820
How does it look?

917
01:00:54.250 --> 01:00:56.119
- It looks fine. - Seung Ho.

918
01:00:56.520 --> 01:00:57.650
Bring the doctor.

919
01:00:57.920 --> 01:01:00.159
Sir, we're going to do a test shoot.

920
01:01:01.020 --> 01:01:03.659
Come this way and stand right here.

921
01:01:04.900 --> 01:01:06.529
- Thank you. - Tell me the truth.

922
01:01:06.659 --> 01:01:09.170
You were that woman who tried to buy sperm, right?

923
01:01:10.029 --> 01:01:11.099
No.

924
01:01:11.869 --> 01:01:14.239
You're a very adventurous woman.

925
01:01:14.369 --> 01:01:15.840
Are you going to keep looking for someone's sperm?

926
01:01:16.270 --> 01:01:18.810
Why don't you just sleep with someone?

927
01:01:19.179 --> 01:01:22.150
Then things will get too complicated.

928
01:01:22.509 --> 01:01:24.710
It'll be a problem even if the guy offers to be the father.

929
01:01:25.349 --> 01:01:26.980
And if I have the baby without telling him,

930
01:01:27.250 --> 01:01:28.619
I might go to the fiery pit.

931
01:01:28.619 --> 01:01:30.250
That's against moral ethics.

932
01:01:31.719 --> 01:01:33.920
I just want to get someone's sperm with their consent...

933
01:01:34.320 --> 01:01:36.259
and have a baby.

934
01:01:36.560 --> 01:01:38.060
What? Like in Hollywood movies?

935
01:01:38.699 --> 01:01:40.929
They get it from a drunk colleague or a friend.

936
01:01:46.900 --> 01:01:48.369
I don't know any guys.

937
01:01:48.369 --> 01:01:49.969
- Hello. - My goodness.

938
01:01:49.969 --> 01:01:52.279
This is the product. It takes you straight to the bathroom.

939
01:01:52.279 --> 01:01:54.179
- Oh, I see. - Here. Take a look.

940
01:03:03.509 --> 01:03:06.320
(Oh My Baby)

941
01:03:06.750 --> 01:03:07.949
Don't look her way.

942
01:03:07.949 --> 01:03:09.549
The look in her eyes is telling me...

943
01:03:09.549 --> 01:03:11.150
that a crazy idea is forming inside her head.

944
01:03:11.150 --> 01:03:12.790
Acknowledge her now and you'll be in trouble.

945
01:03:12.790 --> 01:03:14.520
Where are you three going?

946
01:03:14.520 --> 01:03:16.489
Why would two friends be living together?

947
01:03:16.489 --> 01:03:17.860
It's not wrong at all, you know.

948
01:03:18.190 --> 01:03:20.699
Especially given our close relationship.

949
01:03:20.699 --> 01:03:22.099
He's a dangerous one.

950
01:03:22.199 --> 01:03:23.529
He looks like a con artist.

951
01:03:23.529 --> 01:03:25.900
You think I'll fall for a bad boy...

952
01:03:25.900 --> 01:03:27.799
and burn myself?

953
01:03:27.799 --> 01:03:29.139
Only make mistakes with me, okay?

954
01:03:29.409 --> 01:03:32.110
I don't want you to fall for some random guy because you're lonely.

955
01:03:32.239 --> 01:03:35.679
Younger specimens would have better sperms, right?

